README

This API allows you to manage a list of users stored in a database. You can perform the following CRUD operations:

Create a new user
Retrieve a list of all users or a single user by ID
Update an existing user
Delete a user
Requirements:

PHP 5.5 or higher
MySQL
Endpoints:

GET /users - Retrieves a list of all users
GET /users?id={id} - Retrieves a single user by ID
POST /users - Creates a new user
POST /users?id={id} - Updates an existing user by ID
DELETE /users - Deletes all users
DELETE /users?id={id} - Deletes a single user by ID
To use the API, follow these steps:

Create a database and table
Create a new MySQL database

Create a new table named users with the following fields:

id (int, auto-increment, primary key)
name (varchar)
email (varchar)
Configure the database connection
Open the dbconnect.php file and modify the following variables according to your database configuration:

$db_host - the hostname of your database server
$db_name - the name of your database
$db_user - the username to connect to the database
$db_pass - the password to connect to the database
Upload the API files to your server
Upload all the files to your server.
Test the API
Open a web browser and navigate to the following URL: http://yourdomain.com/users
If everything is configured correctly, you should see a list of all users in JSON format.
Notes:

All data is returned in JSON format.
When creating or updating a user, you must include the name and email fields in the POST request.
When updating a user, you must include the id field in the POST request.